2321
2322double RateControl::clipQscale(Frame* curFrame, RateControlEntry* rce, double q)
2323{
2324 // B-frames are not directly subject to VBV,
2325 // since they are controlled by referenced P-frames' QPs.
2326 double lmin = m_lmin[rce->sliceType];
2327 double lmax = m_lmax[rce->sliceType];
2328 double q0 = q;
2329 if (m_isVbv && m_currentSatd > 0 && curFrame)
2330 {
2331 if (m_param->lookaheadDepth || m_param->rc.cuTree ||
2332 (m_param->scenecutThreshold || m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut) ||
2333 (m_param->bFrameAdaptive && m_param->bframes))
2334 {
2335 /* Lookahead VBV: If lookahead is done, raise the quantizer as necessary
2336 * such that no frames in the lookahead overflow and such that the buffer
2337 * is in a reasonable state by the end of the lookahead. */
2338 int loopTerminate = 0;
2339 /* Avoid an infinite loop. */
2340 for (int iterations = 0; iterations < 1000 && loopTerminate != 3; iterations++)
2341 {
2342 double frameQ[3];
2343 double curBits;
2344 curBits = predictSize(&m_pred[m_predType], q, (double)m_currentSatd);
2345 double bufferFillCur = m_bufferFill - curBits;
2346 double targetFill;
2347 double totalDuration = m_frameDuration;
2348 frameQ[P_SLICE] = m_sliceType == I_SLICE ? q * m_param->rc.ipFactor : (m_sliceType == B_SLICE ? q / m_param->rc.pbFactor : q);
2349 frameQ[B_SLICE] = frameQ[P_SLICE] * m_param->rc.pbFactor;
2350 frameQ[I_SLICE] = frameQ[P_SLICE] / m_param->rc.ipFactor;
2351 /* Loop over the planned future frames. */
2352 bool iter = true;
2353 for (int j = 0; bufferFillCur >= 0 && iter ; j++)
2354 {
2355 int type = curFrame->m_lowres.plannedType[j];
2356 if (type == X265_TYPE_AUTO || totalDuration >= 1.0)
2357 break;
2358 totalDuration += m_frameDuration;
2359 double wantedFrameSize = m_vbvMaxRate * m_frameDuration;
2360 if (bufferFillCur + wantedFrameSize <= m_bufferSize)
2361 bufferFillCur += wantedFrameSize;
2362 int64_t satd = curFrame->m_lowres.plannedSatd[j] >> (X265_DEPTH - 8);
2363 type = IS_X265_TYPE_I(type) ? I_SLICE : IS_X265_TYPE_B(type) ? B_SLICE : P_SLICE;
2364 int predType = getPredictorType(curFrame->m_lowres.plannedType[j], type);
2365 curBits = predictSize(&m_pred[predType], frameQ[type], (double)satd);
2366 bufferFillCur -= curBits;
2367 if (!m_param->bResetZoneConfig && ((uint64_t)j == (m_param->reconfigWindowSize - 1)))
2368 iter = false;
2369 }
2370 if (rce->vbvEndAdj)
2371 {
2372 bool loopBreak = false;
2373 double bufferDiff = m_param->vbvBufferEnd - (m_bufferFill / m_bufferSize);
2374 rce->targetFill = m_bufferFill + m_bufferSize * (bufferDiff / (m_param->totalFrames - rce->encodeOrder));
2375 if (bufferFillCur < rce->targetFill)
2376 {
2377 q *= 1.01;
2378 loopTerminate |= 1;
2379 loopBreak = true;
2380 }
2381 if (bufferFillCur > m_param->vbvBufferEnd * m_bufferSize)
2382 {
2383 q /= 1.01;
2384 loopTerminate |= 2;
2385 loopBreak = true;
2386 }
2387 if (!loopBreak)
2388 break;
2389 }
2390 else
2391 {
2392 /* Try to get the buffer at least 50% filled, but don't set an impossible goal. */
2393 double finalDur = 1;
2394 if (m_param->rc.bStrictCbr)
2395 {
2396 finalDur = x265_clip3(0.4, 1.0, totalDuration);
2397 }
2398 targetFill = X265_MIN(m_bufferFill + totalDuration * m_vbvMaxRate * 0.5, m_bufferSize * (1 - m_minBufferFill * finalDur));
2399 if (bufferFillCur < targetFill)
2400 {
2401 q *= 1.01;
2402 loopTerminate |= 1;
2403 continue;
2404 }
2405 /* Try to get the buffer not more than 80% filled, but don't set an impossible goal. */
2406
2407 targetFill = x265_clip3(m_bufferSize * (1 - m_maxBufferFill * finalDur), m_bufferSize, m_bufferFill - totalDuration * m_vbvMaxRate * 0.5);
2408 if ((m_isCbr || m_2pass) && bufferFillCur > targetFill && !m_isSceneTransition)
2409 {
2410 q /= 1.01;
2411 loopTerminate |= 2;
2412 continue;
2413 }
2414 break;
2415 }
2416 }
2417 q = X265_MAX(q0 / 2, q);
2418 }
2419 else
2420 {
2421 /* Fallback to old purely-reactive algorithm: no lookahead. */
2422 if ((m_sliceType == P_SLICE || m_sliceType == B_SLICE ||
2423 (m_sliceType == I_SLICE && m_lastNonBPictType == I_SLICE)) &&
2424 m_bufferFill / m_bufferSize < m_minBufferFill)
2425 {
2426 q /= x265_clip3(0.5, 1.0, 2.0 * m_bufferFill / m_bufferSize);
2427 }
2428 // Now a hard threshold to make sure the frame fits in VBV.
2429 // This one is mostly for I-frames.
2430 double bits = predictSize(&m_pred[m_predType], q, (double)m_currentSatd);
2431
2432 // For small VBVs, allow the frame to use up the entire VBV.
2433 double maxFillFactor;
2434 maxFillFactor = m_bufferSize >= 5 * m_bufferRate ? 2 : 1;
2435 // For single-frame VBVs, request that the frame use up the entire VBV.
2436 double minFillFactor = m_singleFrameVbv ? 1 : 2;
2437
2438 for (int iterations = 0; iterations < 10; iterations++)
2439 {
2440 double qf = 1.0;
2441 if (bits > m_bufferFill / maxFillFactor)
2442 qf = x265_clip3(0.2, 1.0, m_bufferFill / (maxFillFactor * bits));
2443 q /= qf;
2444 bits *= qf;
2445 if (bits < m_bufferRate / minFillFactor)
2446 q *= bits * minFillFactor / m_bufferRate;
2447 bits = predictSize(&m_pred[m_predType], q, (double)m_currentSatd);
2448 }
2449
2450 q = X265_MAX(q0, q);
2451 }
2452
2453 /* Apply MinCR restrictions */
2454 double pbits = predictSize(&m_pred[m_predType], q, (double)m_currentSatd);
2455 if (pbits > rce->frameSizeMaximum)
2456 q *= pbits / rce->frameSizeMaximum;
2457 /* To detect frames that are more complex in SATD costs compared to prev window, yet
2458 * lookahead vbv reduces its qscale by half its value. Be on safer side and avoid drastic
2459 * qscale reductions for frames high in complexity */
2460 bool mispredCheck = rce->movingAvgSum && m_currentSatd >= rce->movingAvgSum && q <= q0 / 2;
2461 if (!m_isCbr || ((m_isAbr || m_2pass) && mispredCheck))
2462 q = X265_MAX(q0, q);
2463
2464 if (m_rateFactorMaxIncrement)
2465 {
2466 double qpNoVbv = x265_qScale2qp(q0);
2467 double qmax = X265_MIN(lmax,x265_qp2qScale(qpNoVbv + m_rateFactorMaxIncrement));
2468 return x265_clip3(lmin, qmax, q);
2469 }
2470 }
2471 if (!curFrame && m_2pass)
2472 {
2473 double min = log(lmin);
2474 double max = log(lmax);
2475 q = (log(q) - min) / (max - min) - 0.5;
2476 q = 1.0 / (1.0 + exp(-4 * q));
2477 q = q*(max - min) + min;
2478 return exp(q);
2479 }
2480 return x265_clip3(lmin, lmax, q);
2481}
2482
2483double RateControl::predictRowsSizeSum(Frame* curFrame, RateControlEntry* rce, double qpVbv, int32_t& encodedBitsSoFar)
2484{
2485 uint32_t rowSatdCostSoFar = 0, totalSatdBits = 0;
2486 encodedBitsSoFar = 0;
2487
2488 double qScale = x265_qp2qScale(qpVbv);
2489 FrameData& curEncData = *curFrame->m_encData;
2490 int picType = curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType;
2491 Frame* refFrame = curEncData.m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][0];
2492
2493 uint32_t maxRows = curEncData.m_slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight;
2494 uint32_t maxCols = curEncData.m_slice->m_sps->numCuInWidth;
2495
2496 for (uint32_t row = 0; row < maxRows; row++)
2497 {
2498 encodedBitsSoFar += curEncData.m_rowStat[row].encodedBits;
2499 rowSatdCostSoFar = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowSatd;
2500 uint32_t satdCostForPendingCus = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].satdForVbv - rowSatdCostSoFar;
2501 satdCostForPendingCus >>= X265_DEPTH - 8;
2502 if (satdCostForPendingCus > 0)
2503 {
2504 double pred_s = predictSize(rce->rowPred[0], qScale, satdCostForPendingCus);
2505 uint32_t refRowSatdCost = 0, refRowBits = 0, intraCostForPendingCus = 0;
2506 double refQScale = 0;
2507
2508 if (picType != I_SLICE && !m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)
2509 {
2510 FrameData& refEncData = *refFrame->m_encData;
2511 uint32_t endCuAddr = maxCols * (row + 1);
2512 uint32_t startCuAddr = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].numEncodedCUs;
2513 if (startCuAddr)
2514 {
2515 for (uint32_t cuAddr = startCuAddr + 1 ; cuAddr < endCuAddr; cuAddr++)
2516 {
2517 refRowSatdCost += refEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].vbvCost;
2518 refRowBits += refEncData.m_cuStat[cuAddr].totalBits;
2519 }
2520 }
2521 else
2522 {
2523 refRowBits = refEncData.m_rowStat[row].encodedBits;
2524 refRowSatdCost = refEncData.m_rowStat[row].satdForVbv;
2525 }
2526
2527 refRowSatdCost >>= X265_DEPTH - 8;
2528 refQScale = refEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowQpScale;
2529 }
2530
2531 if (picType == I_SLICE || qScale >= refQScale)
2532 {
2533 if (picType == P_SLICE
2534 && refFrame
2535 && refFrame->m_encData->m_slice->m_sliceType == picType
2536 && refQScale > 0
2537 && refRowBits > 0
2538 && !m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)
2539 {
2540 if (abs((int32_t)(refRowSatdCost - satdCostForPendingCus)) < (int32_t)satdCostForPendingCus / 2)
2541 {
2542 double predTotal = refRowBits * satdCostForPendingCus / refRowSatdCost * refQScale / qScale;
2543 totalSatdBits += (int32_t)((pred_s + predTotal) * 0.5);
2544 continue;
2545 }
2546 }
2547 totalSatdBits += (int32_t)pred_s;
2548 }
2549 else if (picType == P_SLICE)
2550 {
2551 intraCostForPendingCus = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].intraSatdForVbv - curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowIntraSatd;
2552 intraCostForPendingCus >>= X265_DEPTH - 8;
2553 /* Our QP is lower than the reference! */
2554 double pred_intra = predictSize(rce->rowPred[1], qScale, intraCostForPendingCus);
2555 /* Sum: better to overestimate than underestimate by using only one of the two predictors. */
2556 totalSatdBits += (int32_t)(pred_intra + pred_s);
2557 }
2558 else
2559 totalSatdBits += (int32_t)pred_s;
2560 }
2561 }
2562
2563 return totalSatdBits + encodedBitsSoFar;
2564}
2565
2566int RateControl::rowVbvRateControl(Frame* curFrame, uint32_t row, RateControlEntry* rce, double& qpVbv, uint32_t* m_sliceBaseRow, uint32_t sliceId)
2567{
2568 FrameData& curEncData = *curFrame->m_encData;
2569 double qScaleVbv = x265_qp2qScale(qpVbv);
2570 uint64_t rowSatdCost = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowSatd;
2571 double encodedBits = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].encodedBits;
2572
2573 rowSatdCost >>= X265_DEPTH - 8;
2574 updatePredictor(rce->rowPred[0], qScaleVbv, (double)rowSatdCost, encodedBits);
2575 if (curEncData.m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE && !m_param->rc.bEnableConstVbv)
2576 {
2577 Frame* refFrame = curEncData.m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][0];
2578 if (qpVbv < refFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[row].rowQp)
2579 {
2580 uint64_t intraRowSatdCost = curEncData.m_rowStat[row].rowIntraSatd;
2581 intraRowSatdCost >>= X265_DEPTH - 8;
2582 updatePredictor(rce->rowPred[1], qScaleVbv, (double)intraRowSatdCost, encodedBits);
2583 }
2584 }
2585
2586 int canReencodeRow = 1;
2587 /* tweak quality based on difference from predicted size */
2588 double prevRowQp = qpVbv;
2589 double qpAbsoluteMax = m_param->rc.qpMax;
2590 double qpAbsoluteMin = m_param->rc.qpMin;
2591 if (m_rateFactorMaxIncrement)
2592 qpAbsoluteMax = X265_MIN(qpAbsoluteMax, rce->qpNoVbv + m_rateFactorMaxIncrement);
2593
2594 if (m_rateFactorMaxDecrement)
2595 qpAbsoluteMin = X265_MAX(qpAbsoluteMin, rce->qpNoVbv - m_rateFactorMaxDecrement);
2596
2597 double qpMax = X265_MIN(prevRowQp + m_param->rc.qpStep, qpAbsoluteMax);
2598 double qpMin = X265_MAX(prevRowQp - m_param->rc.qpStep, qpAbsoluteMin);
2599 double stepSize = 0.5;
2600 double bufferLeftPlanned = rce->bufferFill - rce->frameSizePlanned;
2601
2602 const SPS& sps = *curEncData.m_slice->m_sps;
2603 double maxFrameError = X265_MAX(0.05, 1.0 / sps.numCuInHeight);
2604
2605 if (row < m_sliceBaseRow[sliceId + 1] - 1)
2606 {
2607 /* More threads means we have to be more cautious in letting ratecontrol use up extra bits. */
2608 double rcTol = bufferLeftPlanned / m_param->frameNumThreads * m_rateTolerance;
2609 int32_t encodedBitsSoFar = 0;
2610 double accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2611 double vbvEndBias = 0.95;
2612
2613 /* * Don't increase the row QPs until a sufficent amount of the bits of
2614 * the frame have been processed, in case a flat area at the top of the
2615 * frame was measured inaccurately. */
2616 if (encodedBitsSoFar < 0.05f * rce->frameSizePlanned)
2617 qpMax = qpAbsoluteMax = prevRowQp;
2618
2619 if (rce->sliceType != I_SLICE || (m_param->rc.bStrictCbr && rce->poc > 0))
2620 rcTol *= 0.5;
2621
2622 if (!m_isCbr)
2623 qpMin = X265_MAX(qpMin, rce->qpNoVbv);
2624
2625 double totalBitsNeeded = m_wantedBitsWindow;
2626 if (m_param->totalFrames)
2627 totalBitsNeeded = (m_param->totalFrames * m_bitrate) / m_fps;
2628 double abrOvershoot = (accFrameBits + m_totalBits - m_wantedBitsWindow) / totalBitsNeeded;
2629
2630 while (qpVbv < qpMax
2631 && (((accFrameBits > rce->frameSizePlanned + rcTol) ||
2632 (rce->bufferFill - accFrameBits < bufferLeftPlanned * 0.5) ||
2633 (accFrameBits > rce->frameSizePlanned && qpVbv < rce->qpNoVbv) ||
2634 (rce->vbvEndAdj && ((rce->bufferFill - accFrameBits) < (rce->targetFill * vbvEndBias))))
2635 && (!m_param->rc.bStrictCbr ? 1 : abrOvershoot > 0.1)))
2636 {
2637 qpVbv += stepSize;
2638 accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2639 abrOvershoot = (accFrameBits + m_totalBits - m_wantedBitsWindow) / totalBitsNeeded;
2640 }
2641
2642 while (qpVbv > qpMin
2643 && (qpVbv > curEncData.m_rowStat[0].rowQp || m_singleFrameVbv)
2644 && (((accFrameBits < rce->frameSizePlanned * 0.8f && qpVbv <= prevRowQp)
2645 || accFrameBits < (rce->bufferFill - m_bufferSize + m_bufferRate) * 1.1
2646 || (rce->vbvEndAdj && ((rce->bufferFill - accFrameBits) > (rce->targetFill * vbvEndBias))))
2647 && (!m_param->rc.bStrictCbr ? 1 : abrOvershoot < 0)))
2648 {
2649 qpVbv -= stepSize;
2650 accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2651 abrOvershoot = (accFrameBits + m_totalBits - m_wantedBitsWindow) / totalBitsNeeded;
2652 }
2653
2654 if (m_param->rc.bStrictCbr && m_param->totalFrames)
2655 {
2656 double timeDone = (double)(m_framesDone) / m_param->totalFrames;
2657 while (qpVbv < qpMax && (qpVbv < rce->qpNoVbv + (m_param->rc.qpStep * timeDone)) &&
2658 (timeDone > 0.75 && abrOvershoot > 0))
2659 {
2660 qpVbv += stepSize;
2661 accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2662 abrOvershoot = (accFrameBits + m_totalBits - m_wantedBitsWindow) / totalBitsNeeded;
2663 }
2664 if (qpVbv > curEncData.m_rowStat[0].rowQp &&
2665 abrOvershoot < -0.1 && timeDone > 0.5 && accFrameBits < rce->frameSizePlanned - rcTol)
2666 {
2667 qpVbv -= stepSize;
2668 accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2669 }
2670 }
2671
2672 /* avoid VBV underflow or MinCr violation */
2673 while ((qpVbv < qpAbsoluteMax)
2674 && ((rce->bufferFill - accFrameBits < m_bufferRate * maxFrameError) ||
2675 (rce->frameSizeMaximum - accFrameBits < rce->frameSizeMaximum * maxFrameError)))
2676 {
2677 qpVbv += stepSize;
2678 accFrameBits = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2679 }
2680
2681 rce->frameSizeEstimated = accFrameBits;
2682
2683 /* If the current row was large enough to cause a large QP jump, try re-encoding it. */
2684 if (qpVbv > qpMax && prevRowQp < qpMax && canReencodeRow)
2685 {
2686 /* Bump QP to halfway in between... close enough. */
2687 qpVbv = x265_clip3(prevRowQp + 1.0f, qpMax, (prevRowQp + qpVbv) * 0.5);
2688 return -1;
2689 }
2690
2691 if (m_param->rc.rfConstantMin)
2692 {
2693 if (qpVbv < qpMin && prevRowQp > qpMin && canReencodeRow)
2694 {
2695 qpVbv = x265_clip3(qpMin, prevRowQp, (prevRowQp + qpVbv) * 0.5);
2696 return -1;
2697 }
2698 }
2699 }
2700 else
2701 {
2702 int32_t encodedBitsSoFar = 0;
2703 rce->frameSizeEstimated = predictRowsSizeSum(curFrame, rce, qpVbv, encodedBitsSoFar);
2704
2705 /* Last-ditch attempt: if the last row of the frame underflowed the VBV,
2706 * try again. */
2707 if ((rce->frameSizeEstimated > (rce->bufferFill - m_bufferRate * maxFrameError) &&
2708 qpVbv < qpMax && canReencodeRow))
2709 {
2710 qpVbv = qpMax;
2711 return -1;
2712 }
2713 }
2714 return 0;
2715}
2716
2717/* modify the bitrate curve from pass1 for one frame */
2718double RateControl::getQScale(RateControlEntry *rce, double rateFactor)
2719{
2720 double q;
2721
2722 if (m_param->rc.cuTree && !m_param->rc.hevcAq)
2723 {
2724 // Scale and units are obtained from rateNum and rateDenom for videos with fixed frame rates.
2725 double timescale = (double)m_param->fpsDenom / (2 * m_param->fpsNum);
2726 q = pow(BASE_FRAME_DURATION / CLIP_DURATION(2 * timescale), 1 - m_param->rc.qCompress);
2727 }
2728 else
2729 q = pow(rce->blurredComplexity, 1 - m_param->rc.qCompress);
2730
2731 // avoid NaN's in the Rceq
2732 if (rce->coeffBits + rce->mvBits == 0)
2733 q = m_lastQScaleFor[rce->sliceType];
2734 else
2735 {
2736 m_lastRceq = q;
2737 q /= rateFactor;
2738 }
2739
2740 return q;
2741}
2742
2743void RateControl::updatePredictor(Predictor *p, double q, double var, double bits)
2744{
2745 if (var < 10)
2746 return;
2747 const double range = 2;
2748 double old_coeff = p->coeff / p->count;
2749 double old_offset = p->offset / p->count;
2750 double new_coeff = X265_MAX((bits * q - old_offset) / var, p->coeffMin );
2751 double new_coeff_clipped = x265_clip3(old_coeff / range, old_coeff * range, new_coeff);
2752 double new_offset = bits * q - new_coeff_clipped * var;
2753 if (new_offset >= 0)
2754 new_coeff = new_coeff_clipped;
2755 else
2756 new_offset = 0;
2757 p->count *= p->decay;
2758 p->coeff *= p->decay;
2759 p->offset *= p->decay;
2760 p->count++;
2761 p->coeff += new_coeff;
2762 p->offset += new_offset;
2763}
2764
2765int RateControl::updateVbv(int64_t bits, RateControlEntry* rce)
2766{
2767 int predType = rce->sliceType;
2768 int filler = 0;
2769 double bufferBits;
2770 predType = rce->sliceType == B_SLICE && rce->keptAsRef ? 3 : predType;
2771 if (rce->lastSatd >= m_ncu && rce->encodeOrder >= m_lastPredictorReset)
2772 updatePredictor(&m_pred[predType], x265_qp2qScale(rce->qpaRc), (double)rce->lastSatd, (double)bits);
2773 if (!m_isVbv)
2774 return 0;
2775
2776 m_bufferFillFinal -= bits;
2777
2778 if (m_bufferFillFinal < 0)
2779 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "poc:%d, VBV underflow (%.0f bits)\n", rce->poc, m_bufferFillFinal);
2780
2781 m_bufferFillFinal = X265_MAX(m_bufferFillFinal, 0);
2782 m_bufferFillFinal += rce->bufferRate;
2783 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
2784 m_unclippedBufferFillFinal = m_bufferFillFinal;
2785
2786 if (m_param->rc.bStrictCbr)
2787 {
2788 if (m_bufferFillFinal > m_bufferSize)
2789 {
2790 filler = (int)(m_bufferFillFinal - m_bufferSize);
2791 filler += FILLER_OVERHEAD * 8;
2792 }
2793 m_bufferFillFinal -= filler;
2794 bufferBits = X265_MIN(bits + filler + m_bufferExcess, rce->bufferRate);
2795 m_bufferExcess = X265_MAX(m_bufferExcess - bufferBits + bits + filler, 0);
2796 m_bufferFillActual += bufferBits - bits - filler;
2797 }
2798 else
2799 {
2800 m_bufferFillFinal = X265_MIN(m_bufferFillFinal, m_bufferSize);
2801 bufferBits = X265_MIN(bits + m_bufferExcess, rce->bufferRate);
2802 m_bufferExcess = X265_MAX(m_bufferExcess - bufferBits + bits, 0);
2803 m_bufferFillActual += bufferBits - bits;
2804 m_bufferFillActual = X265_MIN(m_bufferFillActual, m_bufferSize);
2805 }
2806 return filler;
2807}
2808
2809/* After encoding one frame, update rate control state */
2810int RateControl::rateControlEnd(Frame* curFrame, int64_t bits, RateControlEntry* rce, int *filler)
2811{
2812 int orderValue = m_startEndOrder.get();
2813 int endOrdinal = (rce->encodeOrder + m_param->frameNumThreads) * 2 - 1;
2814 while (orderValue < endOrdinal && !m_bTerminated)
2815 {
2816 /* no more frames are being encoded, so fake the start event if we would
2817 * have blocked on it. Note that this does not enforce rateControlEnd()
2818 * ordering during flush, but this has no impact on the outputs */
2819 if (m_finalFrameCount && orderValue >= 2 * m_finalFrameCount)
2820 break;
2821 orderValue = m_startEndOrder.waitForChange(orderValue);
2822 }
2823
2824 FrameData& curEncData = *curFrame->m_encData;
2825 int64_t actualBits = bits;
2826 Slice *slice = curEncData.m_slice;
2827 bool bEnableDistOffset = m_param->analysisMultiPassDistortion && m_param->rc.bStatRead;
2828
2829 if (m_param->rc.aqMode || m_isVbv || m_param->bAQMotion || bEnableDistOffset)
2830 {
2831 if (m_isVbv && !(m_2pass && m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CRF))
2832 {
2833 double avgQpRc = 0;
2834 /* determine avg QP decided by VBV rate control */
2835 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight; i++)
2836 avgQpRc += curEncData.m_rowStat[i].sumQpRc;
2837
2838 avgQpRc /= slice->m_sps->numCUsInFrame;
2839 curEncData.m_avgQpRc = x265_clip3((double)m_param->rc.qpMin, (double)m_param->rc.qpMax, avgQpRc);
2840 rce->qpaRc = curEncData.m_avgQpRc;
2841 }
2842
2843 if (m_param->rc.aqMode || m_param->bAQMotion || bEnableDistOffset)
2844 {
2845 double avgQpAq = 0;
2846 /* determine actual avg encoded QP, after AQ/cutree/distortion adjustments */
2847 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < slice->m_sps->numCuInHeight; i++)
2848 avgQpAq += curEncData.m_rowStat[i].sumQpAq;
2849
2850 avgQpAq /= (slice->m_sps->numCUsInFrame * m_param->num4x4Partitions);
2851 curEncData.m_avgQpAq = avgQpAq;
2852 }
2853 else
2854 curEncData.m_avgQpAq = curEncData.m_avgQpRc;
2855 }
2856
2857 if (m_isAbr)
2858 {
2859 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_ABR && !m_param->rc.bStatRead)
2860 checkAndResetABR(rce, true);
2861 }
2862 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode == X265_RC_CRF)
2863 {
2864 double crfVal, qpRef = curEncData.m_avgQpRc;
2865 bool is2passCrfChange = false;
2866 if (m_2pass)
2867 {
2868 if (fabs(curEncData.m_avgQpRc - rce->qpPrev) > 0.1)
2869 {
2870 qpRef = rce->qpPrev;
2871 is2passCrfChange = true;
2872 }
2873 }
2874 if (is2passCrfChange || fabs(qpRef - rce->qpNoVbv) > 0.5)
2875 {
2876 double crfFactor = rce->qRceq /x265_qp2qScale(qpRef);
2877 double baseCplx = m_ncu * (m_param->bframes ? 120 : 80);
2878 double mbtree_offset = m_param->rc.cuTree ? (1.0 - m_param->rc.qCompress) * 13.5 : 0;
2879 crfVal = x265_qScale2qp(pow(baseCplx, 1 - m_qCompress) / crfFactor) - mbtree_offset;
2880 }
2881 else
2882 crfVal = rce->sliceType == I_SLICE ? m_param->rc.rfConstant - m_ipOffset :
2883 (rce->sliceType == B_SLICE ? m_param->rc.rfConstant + m_pbOffset : m_param->rc.rfConstant);
2884
2885 curEncData.m_rateFactor = crfVal;
2886 }
2887
2888 if (m_isAbr && !m_isAbrReset)
2889 {
2890 /* amortize part of each I slice over the next several frames, up to
2891 * keyint-max, to avoid over-compensating for the large I slice cost */
2892 if (!m_param->rc.bStatWrite && !m_param->rc.bStatRead)
2893 {
2894 if (rce->sliceType == I_SLICE)
2895 {
2896 /* previous I still had a residual; roll it into the new loan */
2897 if (m_residualFrames)
2898 bits += m_residualCost * m_residualFrames;
2899 m_residualFrames = X265_MIN((int)rce->amortizeFrames, m_param->keyframeMax);
2900 m_residualCost = (int)((bits * rce->amortizeFraction) / m_residualFrames);
2901 bits -= m_residualCost * m_residualFrames;
2902 }
2903 else if (m_residualFrames)
2904 {
2905 bits += m_residualCost;
2906 m_residualFrames--;
2907 }
2908 }
2909 if (rce->sliceType != B_SLICE)
2910 {
2911 /* The factor 1.5 is to tune up the actual bits, otherwise the cplxrSum is scaled too low
2912 * to improve short term compensation for next frame. */
2913 m_cplxrSum += (bits * x265_qp2qScale(rce->qpaRc) / rce->qRceq) - (rce->rowCplxrSum);
2914 }
2915 else
2916 {
2917 /* Depends on the fact that B-frame's QP is an offset from the following P-frame's.
2918 * Not perfectly accurate with B-refs, but good enough. */
2919 m_cplxrSum += (bits * x265_qp2qScale(rce->qpaRc) / (rce->qRceq * fabs(m_param->rc.pbFactor))) - (rce->rowCplxrSum);
2920 }
2921 m_wantedBitsWindow += m_frameDuration * m_bitrate;
2922 m_totalBits += bits - rce->rowTotalBits;
2923 m_encodedBits += actualBits;
2924 int pos = m_sliderPos - m_param->frameNumThreads;
2925 if (pos >= 0)
2926 m_encodedBitsWindow[pos % s_slidingWindowFrames] = actualBits;
2927 if(rce->sliceType != I_SLICE)
2928 {
2929 int qp = int (rce->qpaRc + 0.5);
2930 m_qpToEncodedBits[qp] = m_qpToEncodedBits[qp] == 0 ? actualBits : (m_qpToEncodedBits[qp] + actualBits) * 0.5;
2931 }
2932 curFrame->m_rcData->wantedBitsWindow = m_wantedBitsWindow;
2933 curFrame->m_rcData->cplxrSum = m_cplxrSum;
2934 curFrame->m_rcData->totalBits = m_totalBits;
2935 curFrame->m_rcData->encodedBits = m_encodedBits;
2936 }
2937
2938 if (m_2pass)
2939 {
2940 m_expectedBitsSum += qScale2bits(rce, x265_qp2qScale(rce->newQp));
2941 m_totalBits += bits - rce->rowTotalBits;
2942 }
2943
2944 if (m_isVbv)
2945 {
2946 *filler = updateVbv(actualBits, rce);
2947
2948 curFrame->m_rcData->bufferFillFinal = m_bufferFillFinal;
2949 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
2950 {
2951 curFrame->m_rcData->coeff[i] = m_pred[i].coeff;
2952 curFrame->m_rcData->count[i] = m_pred[i].count;
2953 curFrame->m_rcData->offset[i] = m_pred[i].offset;
2954 }
2955 if (m_param->bEmitHRDSEI)
2956 {
2957 const VUI *vui = &curEncData.m_slice->m_sps->vuiParameters;
2958 const HRDInfo *hrd = &vui->hrdParameters;
2959 const TimingInfo *time = &vui->timingInfo;
2960 if (!curFrame->m_poc)
2961 {
2962 // first access unit initializes the HRD
2963 rce->hrdTiming->cpbInitialAT = 0;
2964 rce->hrdTiming->cpbRemovalTime = m_nominalRemovalTime = (double)m_bufPeriodSEI.m_initialCpbRemovalDelay / 90000;
2965 }
2966 else
2967 {
2968 rce->hrdTiming->cpbRemovalTime = m_nominalRemovalTime + (double)rce->picTimingSEI->m_auCpbRemovalDelay * time->numUnitsInTick / time->timeScale;
2969 double cpbEarliestAT = rce->hrdTiming->cpbRemovalTime - (double)m_bufPeriodSEI.m_initialCpbRemovalDelay / 90000;
2970 if (!curFrame->m_lowres.bKeyframe)
2971 cpbEarliestAT -= (double)m_bufPeriodSEI.m_initialCpbRemovalDelayOffset / 90000;
2972
2973 rce->hrdTiming->cpbInitialAT = hrd->cbrFlag ? m_prevCpbFinalAT : X265_MAX(m_prevCpbFinalAT, cpbEarliestAT);
2974 }
2975 int filler_bits = *filler ? (*filler - START_CODE_OVERHEAD * 8) : 0;
2976 uint32_t cpbsizeUnscale = hrd->cpbSizeValue << (hrd->cpbSizeScale + CPB_SHIFT);
2977 rce->hrdTiming->cpbFinalAT = m_prevCpbFinalAT = rce->hrdTiming->cpbInitialAT + (actualBits + filler_bits)/ cpbsizeUnscale;
2978 rce->hrdTiming->dpbOutputTime = (double)rce->picTimingSEI->m_picDpbOutputDelay * time->numUnitsInTick / time->timeScale + rce->hrdTiming->cpbRemovalTime;
2979 }
2980 }
2981 rce->isActive = false;
2982 // Allow rateControlStart of next frame only when rateControlEnd of previous frame is over
2983 m_startEndOrder.incr();
2984 return 0;
2985}

3140void RateControl::splitdeltaPOC(char deltapoc[], RateControlEntry *rce)
3141{

3186double RateControl::forwardMasking(Frame* curFrame, double q)
3187{
3188 double qp = x265_qScale2qp(q);
3189 uint32_t maxWindowSize = uint32_t((m_param->fwdScenecutWindow / 1000.0) * (m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom) + 0.5);
3190 uint32_t windowSize = maxWindowSize / 3;
3191 int lastScenecut = m_top->m_rateControl->m_lastScenecut;
3192 int lastIFrame = m_top->m_rateControl->m_lastScenecutAwareIFrame;
3193 double fwdRefQpDelta = double(m_param->fwdRefQpDelta);
3194 double fwdNonRefQpDelta = double(m_param->fwdNonRefQpDelta);
3195 double sliceTypeDelta = SLICE_TYPE_DELTA * fwdRefQpDelta;
3196
3197 //Check whether the current frame is within the forward window
3198 if (curFrame->m_poc > lastScenecut && curFrame->m_poc <= (lastScenecut + int(maxWindowSize)))
3199 curFrame->m_isInsideWindow = FORWARD_WINDOW;
3200 if (curFrame->m_isInsideWindow == FORWARD_WINDOW)
3201 {
3202 if (IS_X265_TYPE_I(curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType) || curFrame->m_lowres.bScenecut)
3203 {
3204 m_top->m_rateControl->m_lastScenecutAwareIFrame = curFrame->m_poc;
3205 }
3206 else if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_P)
3207 {
3208 if (!(lastIFrame > lastScenecut && lastIFrame <= (lastScenecut + int(maxWindowSize))
3209 && curFrame->m_poc >= lastIFrame))
3210 {
3211 //Add offsets corresponding to the window in which the P-frame occurs
3212 if (curFrame->m_poc <= (lastScenecut + int(windowSize)))
3213 qp += WINDOW1_DELTA * (fwdRefQpDelta - sliceTypeDelta);
3214 else if (((curFrame->m_poc) > (lastScenecut + int(windowSize))) && ((curFrame->m_poc) <= (lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))))
3215 qp += WINDOW2_DELTA * (fwdRefQpDelta - sliceTypeDelta);
3216 else if (curFrame->m_poc > lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))
3217 qp += WINDOW3_DELTA * (fwdRefQpDelta - sliceTypeDelta);
3218 }
3219 }
3220 else if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
3221 {
3222 if (!(lastIFrame > lastScenecut && lastIFrame <= (lastScenecut + int(maxWindowSize))
3223 && curFrame->m_poc >= lastIFrame))
3224 {
3225 //Add offsets corresponding to the window in which the B-frame occurs
3226 if (curFrame->m_poc <= (lastScenecut + int(windowSize)))
3227 qp += WINDOW1_DELTA * fwdRefQpDelta;
3228 else if (((curFrame->m_poc) > (lastScenecut + int(windowSize))) && ((curFrame->m_poc) <= (lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))))
3229 qp += WINDOW2_DELTA * fwdRefQpDelta;
3230 else if (curFrame->m_poc > lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))
3231 qp += WINDOW3_DELTA * fwdRefQpDelta;
3232 }
3233 }
3234 else if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
3235 {
3236 if (!(lastIFrame > lastScenecut && lastIFrame <= (lastScenecut + int(maxWindowSize))
3237 && curFrame->m_poc >= lastIFrame))
3238 {
3239 //Add offsets corresponding to the window in which the b-frame occurs
3240 if (curFrame->m_poc <= (lastScenecut + int(windowSize)))
3241 qp += WINDOW1_DELTA * fwdNonRefQpDelta;
3242 else if (((curFrame->m_poc) > (lastScenecut + int(windowSize))) && ((curFrame->m_poc) <= (lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))))
3243 qp += WINDOW2_DELTA * fwdNonRefQpDelta;
3244 else if (curFrame->m_poc > lastScenecut + 2 * int(windowSize))
3245 qp += WINDOW3_DELTA * fwdNonRefQpDelta;
3246 }
3247 }
3248 }
3249
3250 return x265_qp2qScale(qp);

3252double RateControl::backwardMasking(Frame* curFrame, double q)
3253{
3254 double qp = x265_qScale2qp(q);
3255 double fwdRefQpDelta = double(m_param->fwdRefQpDelta);
3256 double bwdRefQpDelta = double(m_param->bwdRefQpDelta);
3257 double bwdNonRefQpDelta = double(m_param->bwdNonRefQpDelta);
3258
3259 if (curFrame->m_isInsideWindow == BACKWARD_WINDOW)
3260 {
3261 if (bwdRefQpDelta < 0)
3262 bwdRefQpDelta = WINDOW3_DELTA * fwdRefQpDelta;
3263 double sliceTypeDelta = SLICE_TYPE_DELTA * bwdRefQpDelta;
3264 if (bwdNonRefQpDelta < 0)
3265 bwdNonRefQpDelta = bwdRefQpDelta + sliceTypeDelta;
3266
3267 if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_P)
3268 qp += bwdRefQpDelta - sliceTypeDelta;
3269 else if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
3270 qp += bwdRefQpDelta;
3271 else if (curFrame->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
3272 qp += bwdNonRefQpDelta;
3273 }
3274
3275 return x265_qp2qScale(qp);
3276}
